owl:Class.terms:description: A social entity pertains to the interaction among individuals and groups.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: social entity

owl:Class.terms:description: A social structure is a social entity which consists of relationships between two or more entities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: social structure

owl:Class.terms:description: An organization is a collective with a complex articulation of tasks, roles and responsibilities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: organization

owl:Class.terms:description: A geographic position is the coordinate of an entity against some geographic coordinate system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: geographic position

owl:Class.terms:description: information content entity is an object that requires some background knowledge or procedure to correctly interpret.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: information content entity

owl:Class.terms:description: A start date is a time instant pertaining to the date of the beginning of a process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: start date

owl:Class.terms:description: An end date is a time instant pertaining to date of the end of a process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: end date

owl:Class.terms:description: A spatial quantity is a quantity obtained from measuring the spatial extent of an entity
owl:Class.rdfs:label: spatial quantity

owl:Class.terms:description: A quantity that extends in single dimension.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: 1D extent quantity

owl:Class.terms:description: depth is the dimensional extent into a plane of a 3D projection of the object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: depth

owl:Class.terms:description: height is the one dimensional extent along the vertical projection of a 3D object from a base plane of reference.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: height

owl:Class.terms:description: length is the longer dimensional extent along a 2D projection of the object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: length

owl:Class.terms:description: width is the shorter dimensional extent perpendicular to a 2D projection of the object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: width

owl:Class.terms:description: thickness is the shortest dimensional extent of a 3D projection of an object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: thickness

owl:Class.terms:description: A quantity that extends in two dimensions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: 2D extent quantity

owl:Class.terms:description: area is a quantity that pertains to the extent of a two-dimensional surface or shape, or planar lamina, in the plane.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: area

owl:Class.terms:description: A perimeter is a length of the outline that surrounds a two-dimensional shape.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: length of perimeter

owl:Class.terms:description: circumference is the length of the outline of a circle or ellipse. it is defined as c = 2*pi*r, where r is the radius.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: circumference

owl:Class.terms:description: A quantity that extends in three dimensions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: 3D extent quantity

owl:Class.terms:description: volume is the quantity of three-dimensional space enclosed by some closed boundary.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: volume

owl:Class.terms:description: A quantity is an informational entity that gives the magnitude of a property.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: quantity

owl:Class.terms:description: A measurement of a spatial location relative to a frame of reference or other objects.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: position

owl:Class.terms:description: orientation is an angle between the bearer and an axis, or the angle between the bearer and another object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: orientation

owl:Class.terms:description: A namespace is an informational entity that defines a logical container for a set of symbols or identifiers.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: namespace

owl:Class.terms:description: A data item consists of information that has been collected/generated towards some purpose.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: data item

owl:Class.terms:description: A measurement value is a quantitative description that reflects the magnitude of some attribute.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: measurement value

owl:Class.terms:description: A coordinate is a measurement of position in n-dimensional space.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: coordinate

owl:Class.terms:description: A Cartesian coordinate is the signed distance of a point to some referent line.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: cartesian coordinate

owl:Class.terms:description: A polar coordinate is a position characterized by a distance from a fixed point and an angle from a fixed direction.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: polar coordinate

owl:Class.terms:description: A unit of measurement is a definite magnitude of a physical quantity, defined and adopted by convention and/or by law, that is used as a standard for measurement of the same physical quantity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: unit of measurement

owl:Class.terms:description: A mathematical entity is an information content entity that are components of a mathematical system or can be defined in mathematical terms.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: mathematical entity

owl:Class.terms:description: A plan is a set of intended actions, through which one expects to achieve a goal.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: plan

owl:Class.terms:description: A generic name is the preferred name provided by manufacturer.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: generic name

owl:Class.terms:description: A language entity implements some language specification for the visual interpretation and is part of some document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: language entity

owl:Class.terms:description: A visual language entity is a language entity that is manifested within the spectrum of light and can be pereceived and processed by a visual system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: visual language entity

owl:Class.terms:description: A figure is a graphical entity which consists of a visual (n-dimentional) arrangement of information entities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: figure

owl:Class.terms:description: An image is an affine projection of a visual entity to a two dimensional surface.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: image

owl:Class.terms:description: A photograph is an image created by light falling on a light-sensitive surface.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: photograph

owl:Class.terms:description: A statistical graph is a figure that displays the relationship among numeric data and/or mathematical functions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: statistical graph

owl:Class.terms:description: A question is a linguistic expression used to make a request for information.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: question

owl:Class.terms:description: A publication is a document that has been made available by a publisher.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: publication

owl:Class.terms:description: A record is a document containing a collection of statements about some entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: record

owl:Class.terms:description: A dataset is a data item that is a collection of data items.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: dataset

owl:Class.terms:description: A specification is a description of the essential technical attributes/requirements for an object or procedure, and may be used to determine that the object / procedure meets its requirements/attributes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: specification

owl:Class.terms:description: An action specification is a specification composed of a sequence of instructions to achieve some objective.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: action specification

owl:Class.terms:description: An algorithm is an effective method expressed as a finite list of well-defined instructions for calculating a function.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: algorithm

owl:Class.terms:description: A software entity is a computational entity that can be interpreted by or directly executed by a processing unit.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: software entity

owl:Class.terms:description: A software method (also called subroutine, subprogram, procedure, method, function, or routine) is software designed to execute a specific task.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: software method

owl:Class.terms:description: A software module is software composed of a collection of software methods.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: software module

owl:Class.terms:description: A software library is software composed of a collection of software modules and/or software methods in a form that can be statically or dynamically linked to some software application.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: software library

owl:Class.terms:description: A software application is software that can be directly executed by some processing unit.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: software application

owl:Class.terms:description: A software interpreter is a software application that executes some specified input software.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: software interpreter

owl:Class.terms:description: A software script is software whose instructions can be executed using a software interpreter.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: software script

owl:Class.terms:description: Language is a language entity which is the result of encoding and decoding information through systematic creation and usage of systems of symbols, each pairing a specific sign with an intended meaning, established through social conventions
owl:Class.rdfs:label: language

owl:Class.terms:description: A symbol is a proposition about what an entity represents.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: symbol

owl:Class.terms:description: A book is a publication composed of a large number of entries.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: book

owl:Class.terms:description: A chapter is a document section of a book or thesis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: chapter

owl:Class.terms:description: A character is a language symbol used to construct words.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: character

owl:Class.terms:description: A novel is a fictitious prose narrative of book length, typically representing character and action with some degree of realism.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: novel

owl:Class.terms:description: A paragraph is a self-contained unit of written discourse consisting of one or more sentences.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: paragraph

owl:Class.terms:description: A document section is a component of a document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: document section

owl:Class.terms:description: A sentence is a grammatical unit consisting of one or more words that bear minimal syntactic relation to the words that precede or follow it.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sentence

owl:Class.terms:description: A word is the smallest free form (an item that may be expressed in isolation with semantic or pragmatic content) in a language.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: word

owl:Class.terms:description: An identifier is a label that specifically refers to (identifies) an entity (instance/type).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: A name is a label used to identify an entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: name

owl:Class.terms:description: A preferred name is the name that is generally used by some organization.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: preferred name

owl:Class.terms:description: A common name is a name that is commonly used.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: common name

owl:Class.terms:description: A brand name is a trademarked and marketed name of a product.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: brand name

owl:Class.terms:description: A scientific name is a name given through scientific nomenclature.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: scientific name

owl:Class.terms:description: A magazine is a periodical that typically contains essays, stories, poems, etc., by many writers, and often photographs and drawings, frequently specializing in a particular subject or area, as hobbies, news, or sports.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: magazine

owl:Class.terms:description: A workflow is an algorithm that is is a depiction of a sequence of operations to achieve one or more objectives.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: workflow

owl:Class.terms:description: An ontology document is a document that contains an ontology.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ontology document

owl:Class.terms:description: A pattern is a generalized representation of some repeatable concrete or informational item.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: pattern

owl:Class.terms:description: A sequence motif is a pattern of nucleotides in a DNA sequence or amino acids in a protein.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sequence motif

owl:Class.terms:description: A descriptor (index term, subject term, subject heading) is a term that captures the essence of the topic of a document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: descriptor

owl:Class.terms:description: A definition is a description that succintly characterizes an entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: definition

owl:Class.terms:description: A description is language entity in which elements of a language (formal or natural) are used to characterize an entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: description

owl:Class.terms:description: A category is a class of entities having particular shared characteristics.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: category

owl:Class.terms:description: A class is a collection of sets which can be unambiguously defined by a property that all its members share.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: class

owl:Class.terms:description: A web service is a software application that can be accessed over a network, such as the Internet, and executed on a remote system hosting the requested services.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: web service

owl:Class.terms:description: A criterion is a specification to describe properties used for evaluation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: criterion

owl:Class.terms:description: An inclusion criterion is a criterion that must be present to satisfy some objective.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: inclusion criterion

owl:Class.terms:description: An exclusion criterion is a criterion that must be absent to satistify the objective.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: exclusion criterion

owl:Class.terms:description: A parameter is variable whose value changes the characteristics of a system or a function.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: parameter

owl:Class.terms:description: A keyword is a descriptor in which the association of the word with the entity facilitates information retrieval.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: keyword

owl:Class.terms:description: A document is a bounded physical or digital representation of a body of information designed with the capacity (and usually intent) to communicate.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: document

owl:Class.terms:description: A list is any enumeration of a set of items.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: list

owl:Class.terms:description: A manuscript is a document prior to publication.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: manuscript

owl:Class.terms:description: A note is a brief document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: note

owl:Class.terms:description: A patent is an information entity granted by a patent issuing authority which confers upon the patenter the sole right to make, use and sell an invention for a set period of time.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: patent

owl:Class.terms:description: An article is a publication that is stand-alone section of a larger work.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: article

owl:Class.terms:description: A blog is a publication accessible at some website and is typically about various experiences.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: blog

owl:Class.terms:description: A book volume is a book that is part of a collection.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: book volume

owl:Class.terms:description: A conference proceedings is a book composed of papers presented at a conference.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: conference proceedings

owl:Class.terms:description: A book series is a collection of books that have been sequentially published.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: book series

owl:Class.terms:description: An edited publication is a publication that has been examined and potentially changed by an editor.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: edited publication

owl:Class.terms:description: A journal is a a peer-reviewed periodical in which scholarship relating to a particular academic discipline is published.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: journal

owl:Class.terms:description: A manual is a document that instructs on the usage of a device.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: manual

owl:Class.terms:description: A periodical is a publication that appears on a regular schedule.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: periodical

owl:Class.terms:description: A newspaper is a periodical publication containing news regarding current events, informative articles, diverse features, editorials, and advertising.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: newspaper

owl:Class.terms:description: A technical report is a publication published by a school or other institution, usually numbered within a series.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: technical report

owl:Class.terms:description: A thesis document is the written research component of a post-secondary institution that contains a statement supported by arguments.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: thesis document

owl:Class.terms:description: An honor's thesis is a thesis prepared as a requirement for an honor's undergraduate degree.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: honor's thesis

owl:Class.terms:description: A Master's thesis is a thesis prepared as a requirement for a Master's degree.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: master's thesis

owl:Class.terms:description: A PhD thesis is a thesis prepared as a requirement for a doctoral degree.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: phd thesis

owl:Class.terms:description: A booklet is a document that lacks a named publisher or sponsoring institution.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: booklet

owl:Class.terms:description: A diary is a document which describes day-to-day experiences.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: diary

owl:Class.terms:description: A bibliographic attribute is an attribute related to publications.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: document component

owl:Class.terms:description: An address is a position that indicates the physical location of some entity using a social convention.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: address

owl:Class.terms:description: An affiliation is a social relation which indicates the partnership between two or more entities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: affiliation

owl:Class.terms:description: A citation is a textual entity which denotes a source described in the bibliography or reference section of a document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: citation

owl:Class.terms:description: A document title is a textual entity that summarizes the topic of the document in one sentence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: document title

owl:Class.terms:description: A reference is a textual entity that describes a single source used in the preparation or development of the work.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: reference

owl:Class.terms:description: A page range denotes the start and end page in some document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: page range

owl:Class.terms:description: A page total is a textual entity that is about the number of pages in some informational entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: page total

owl:Class.terms:description: a label is a term that is associated with some entity
owl:Class.rdfs:label: label

owl:Class.terms:description: A language label is a label that denotes the language of a textual entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: language label

owl:Class.terms:description: A first name is a name that denotes a specific individual between members of a group of individuals, whose members usually share the same surname.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: first name

owl:Class.terms:description: A last name (surname) is a name added to a given name and is part of a personal name and is often the family name.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: last name

owl:Class.terms:description: A personal name is a name to identify an individual person and usually comprises of a first name and a last name.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: personal name

owl:Class.terms:description: A legal name is a name given at birth, or which appears on their birth certificate, marriage certificate, or change of name certificate.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: legal name

owl:Class.terms:description: A title is a textual entity that summarily describes some entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: title

owl:Class.terms:description: A document version is a version of a work in some sequence of derivative works.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: document version

owl:Class.terms:description: An abstract section is a document section that provides brief summary of a document that explains the main argument(s), topic(s) or findings.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: abstract section

owl:Class.terms:description: An acknowledgements section is a document section that identifies individuals, groups or organizations for their support in the development of the work.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: acknowledgements section

owl:Class.terms:description: An author contribution section is a document section that describes the contribution of the authors.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: author contribution section

owl:Class.terms:description: An author section is a document section that lists the contributing authors.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: author section

owl:Class.terms:description: A bibliography section is a document section that is composed of a list of references used in the development of the work.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: bibliography section

owl:Class.terms:description: A copyright section is a document section that contains a notice of copyright.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: copyright section

owl:Class.terms:description: A correspondence section is a document section that contains the details for contacting the corresponding author.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: correspondence section

owl:Class.terms:description: The discussion section is a document section containing a summary of the findings, a reflection on the significance of findings, comparison with related work, among others.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: discussion section

owl:Class.terms:description: An introduction section is a document section that generally provides background, motivation and goals of the work.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: introduction section

owl:Class.terms:description: The materials and methods section is a document section containing a description of the materials and methods used in the study.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: materials and methods section

owl:Class.terms:description: The materials section is a document section containing a description of the materials used in the study.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: materials section

owl:Class.terms:description: The methods section is a document section containing a description of the methods used in the study.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: methods section

owl:Class.terms:description: The results section is a document section describing the main findings of the study.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: results section

owl:Class.terms:description: The table of contents is a document section that lists all sections (and optionally subsections) in a sequential order along with their page number.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: table of contents

owl:Class.terms:description: Implication is a logical operator that holds between a set T of propositions and a proposition B, when every model (or interpretation or valuation) of T is also a model of B.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: implies (->)

owl:Class.terms:description: A namespace label is a short name for a namespace.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: namespace label

owl:Class.terms:description: A logical operator is a unary or binary relation to construct logical expressions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: logical operator

owl:Class.terms:description: AND is a logical operator that has the value true if both of its operands are true, otherwise a value of false.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: conjunction (and)

owl:Class.terms:description: A proposition is a sentence expressing something true or false.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: proposition

owl:Class.terms:description: A dimensionless quantity is a quantity that has no associated unit.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: dimensionless quantity

owl:Class.terms:description: A dimensional quantity is a quantity that has an associated unit.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: dimensional quantity

owl:Class.terms:description: An argument is a set of one or more declarative sentences (or propositions) known as the premises along with another declarative sentence (or proposition) known as the conclusion.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: argument

owl:Class.terms:description: A premise is a proposition of an argument from which the conclusion is drawn.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: premise

owl:Class.terms:description: A conclusion is a proposition which is reached after considering the evidence, arguments or premises.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: conclusion

owl:Class.terms:description: A deductive argument is an argument that asserts that the truth of the conclusion is a logical consequence of the premises.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: deductive argument

owl:Class.terms:description: An inductive argument is an argument that asserts that the truth of the conclusion is supported by the premises.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: inductive argument

owl:Class.terms:description: A sound argument is a valid argument with true premises.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sound argument

owl:Class.terms:description: A valid argument is an argument where the truth of the conclusion is a logical consequence of the premises and (consequently) its corresponding conditional is a necessary truth.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: valid argument

owl:Class.terms:description: An invalid argument is an argument where the truth of the conclusion is false because it is not a logical consequence of the premises.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: invalid argument

owl:Class.terms:description: A term is a word or phrase used to denote one or more entities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: term

owl:Class.terms:description: mass is the quality of the amount of substance.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: mass

owl:Class.terms:description: OR is a logical operator that results in true whenever one or more of its operands are true.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: disjunction (or)

owl:Class.terms:description: NOT is a logical operator in that has the value true if its operand is false.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: negation (not)

owl:Class.terms:description: XOR, also called exclusive disjunction or (symbolized XOR, EOR, EXOR, or ⊕), is a type of logical disjunction on two operands that results in a value of true if exactly one of the operands has a value of true.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: exclusive disjunction (xor)

owl:Class.terms:description: A hypothesis is a proposed explanation for a phenomenon.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: hypothesis

owl:Class.terms:description: An academic organization is a lawfully recognized organization that confers diplomas, degrees and other forms of recognition of academic achievement.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: academic organization

owl:Class.terms:description: A social relation is a social entity that describes a relationship between two or more individuals or groups.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: social relation

owl:Class.terms:description: A set is a collection of entities, for which there may be zero members.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: set

owl:Class.terms:description: A university is an institution of higher education and research which grants academic degrees in a variety of subjects and provides both undergraduate education and postgraduate education.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: university

owl:Class.terms:description: A collection of documents is a non-zero set of documents.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: collection of documents

owl:Class.terms:description: A website is a collection of documents published on the World Wide Web.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: website

owl:Class.terms:description: A movie is a series of images that are displayed in rapid succession to give the impression of movement.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: movie

owl:Class.terms:description: An excerpt is a contiguous or discontiguous portion of a document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: excerpt

owl:Class.terms:description: A quote is a excerpt that is attributed to a particular source.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: quote

owl:Class.terms:description: A geographic image is a photograph of some geographical area.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: geographic image

owl:Class.terms:description: A web page is a document that is published according to World Wide Web standards.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: web page

owl:Class.terms:description: Email message is a digital document that is composed of a header and a body and is transmitted using the SMTP protocol.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: email

owl:Class.terms:description: process number is a number associated with a process that denotes its ordinal position in a set of processes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: process number

owl:Class.terms:description: A letter is a document that contains a personal communication from one part to another.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: letter

owl:Class.terms:description: An edition number is count of a literary work edited and published, as by a certain editor or in a certain manner including being printed during some interval of time.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: edition number

owl:Class.terms:description: volume number is a count of a sequence of periodicals.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: volume number

owl:Class.terms:description: A functional specification is a specification that describes the characteristics of an object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: functional specification

owl:Class.terms:description: A design specification is a specification that provides precise and explicit information about the requirements for a product design.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: design specification

owl:Class.terms:description: A specification for spatial location is an effective specification towards representation spatial position or spatial data.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: spatial specification

owl:Class.terms:description: Longitude is a geographic position that refers to the angle east or west of a reference meridian between the two geographical poles to another meridian that passes through an arbitrary point.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: longitude

owl:Class.terms:description: Latitude is a geographic coordinate which refers to the angle from a point on the Earth's surface to the equatorial plane
owl:Class.rdfs:label: latitude

owl:Class.terms:description: A coordinate system is a specification for spatial location that uses a set of numbers, or coordinates, to uniquely determine the position of a point or other geometric element.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: coordinate system

owl:Class.terms:description: A Cartesian coordinate system specifies each point uniquely in a plane by a pair of numerical coordinates, which are the signed distances from the point to two fixed perpendicular directed lines, measured in the same unit of length.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: cartesian coordinate system

owl:Class.terms:description: A concept is term that refers to a generalization of a set of attributes or entities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: concept

owl:Class.terms:description: A polar coordinate system is a two-dimensional coordinate system in which each point on a plane is determined by a distance from a fixed point and an angle from a fixed direction.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: polar coordinate system

owl:Class.terms:description: A positional description is a description of location using some system or frame of reference.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: positional identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: A cylindrical coordinate system is a three-dimensional coordinate system that specifies point positions by the distance from a chosen reference axis, the direction from the axis relative to a chosen reference direction, and the distance from a chosen reference plane perpendicular to the axis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: cylindrical coordinate system

owl:Class.terms:description: A spherical coordinate system is a coordinate system for three-dimensional space where the position of a point is specified by three numbers: the radial distance of that point from a fixed origin, its polar angle measured from a fixed zenith direction, and the azimuth angle of its orthogonal projection on a reference plane that passes through the origin and is orthogonal to the zenith, measured from a fixed reference direction on that plane.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: spherical coordinate system

owl:Class.terms:description: An OWL ontology is an ontology as specified by the W3C OWL specification.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: OWL ontology

owl:Class.terms:description: A 3D cartesian coordinate is a coordinate that is composed of an x, y and z coordinate.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: 3D cartesian coordinate

owl:Class.terms:description: An objective is a proposition that indicates a planned or anticipated outcome.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: objective

owl:Class.terms:description: purpose is the reason for which something is done or created or for which something exists.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: purpose

owl:Class.terms:description: A belief is a proposition that is believed to be true.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: belief

owl:Class.terms:description: A number is a mathematical object used to count, label, and measure.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: number

owl:Class.terms:description: A variable is a value that may change within the scope of a given problem or set of operations.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: variable

owl:Class.terms:description: An equation is a mathematical statement that asserts the equality of two expressions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: equation

owl:Class.terms:description: time measurement is a measurement value of the duration of some interval of time or a particular instant of time (against some frame of reference).
owl:Class.schema:comment: Time intervals are specified as date/datetime ranges.
owl:Class.resource:example: the duration of my life; the duration of a surgical procedure, the moment of death
owl:Class.rdfs:label: time measurement

owl:Class.terms:description: A file is an information-bearing object that contains a physical embodiment of some information using a particular character encoding.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: file

owl:Class.terms:description: An x cartesian coordinate is the coordinate of an object onto the x-axis of a cartesian coordinate system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: x cartesian coordinate

owl:Class.terms:description: An y cartesian coordinate is the coordinate of an object onto the y-axis of a cartesian coordinate system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: y cartesian coordinate

owl:Class.terms:description: A z cartesian coordinate is the coordinate of an object onto the z-axis of a cartesian coordinate system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: z cartesian coordinate

owl:Class.terms:description: A study group is a group of individuals that are subjects in an observational or intervention study.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: study group

owl:Class.terms:description: A time internval is a contiguous temporal region having some duration.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: time interval

owl:Class.terms:description: A time instant is a temporal region which occurs instantaneously, e.g. having no duration.
owl:Class.resource:example: at this moment; the moment at which a finger is detached in an industrial accident; the moment at which a child is born; the moment of death
owl:Class.rdfs:label: time instant

owl:Class.terms:description: A table is a figure that consists of an ordered arrangement of columns and rows.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: table

owl:Class.terms:description: A scatterplot is a statistical graph which uses Cartesian coordinates to display values for two variables for a set of data. The data is displayed as a collection of points, each having the value of one variable determining the position on the horizontal axis and the value of the other variable determining the position on the vertical axis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: scatterplot

owl:Class.terms:description: A year is a period of time taken by a planet to make one revolution around the sun.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: year

owl:Class.terms:description: A month is a period of time that divides the year.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: month

owl:Class.terms:description: A day is a period of 24 hours.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: day

owl:Class.terms:description: A century is a period of one hundred years.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: century

owl:Class.terms:description: A millenium is a period of 1000 years
owl:Class.rdfs:label: millenium

owl:Class.terms:description: An hour is a period of 60 minutes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: hour

owl:Class.terms:description: A minute is a period of 60 seconds.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: minute

owl:Class.terms:description: A second (symbol: s) is the base unit of time in the International System of Units (SI) and is the second division of the hour by sixty, the first division by 60 being the minute.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: second

owl:Class.terms:description: A 2D cartesian point is a point whose position is specified along two dimensions using Cartesian coordinates.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: 2D cartesian point

owl:Class.terms:description: Altitude is a distance above sea level.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: altitude

owl:Class.terms:description: The center of mass (aka barycenter) is the weighted average location of all the mass in a body or group of bodies.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: center of mass

owl:Class.terms:description: A 3D cartesian point is a point whose position is specified along three dimensions using Cartesian coordinates.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: 3D cartesian point

owl:Class.terms:description: A 1D cartesian point is a point whose position is specified along a single dimension using Cartesian coordinates.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: 1D cartesian point

owl:Class.terms:description: A line graph is a statistical graph in which lines contains the evaluation of functions or individual points connected by line segments.
owl:Class.resource:example: Graph 1 in http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: line graph

owl:Class.terms:description: A bar graph is a statistical graph with rectangular bars of lengths proportional to that value that they represent.
owl:Class.resource:example: Graphs 3,4,5 in http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: bar graph

owl:Class.terms:description: A horizontal bar graph is a bar graph in which the rectangular bars are horizontally oriented in space.
owl:Class.resource:example: Graph 3 in http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: horizontal bar graph

owl:Class.terms:description: A vertical bar graph is a bar graph in which the rectangular bars are vertically oriented in space.
owl:Class.resource:example: Graph 4,5 in http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: vertical bar graph

owl:Class.terms:description: A stacked bar graph is a bar graph in which each rectangular bar is partioned by the categorical value of each series of data.
owl:Class.resource:example: Graphs 6,7 in http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: stacked bar graph

owl:Class.terms:description: A line-bar graph statistical graph that contains both lines and bars.
owl:Class.resource:example: Graph 8 in http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: line-bar graph

owl:Class.terms:description: A figure part is a part of a figure.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: figure part

owl:Class.terms:description: A plot is a part of a figure that corresponds to the spatial region between the set of axes.
owl:Class.resource:example: The square portion of the chart bounded by lines that overlap with the two axes in Graph 1 of http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: plot

owl:Class.terms:description: An axis is a line segment that is part of a statistical graph in which the position along the line corresponds to a numeric or categorical value.
owl:Class.schema:comment: The value of a plotted geometric objects (e.g. point) can be obtained from the perpendicular projection of the position of the object onto the axis. Axis may also be associated with a textual description of what the values on the axis represents.
owl:Class.resource:example: The left vertical and bottom horizontal lines with tickmarks in Graph 1 http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: axis

owl:Class.terms:description: A Cartesian coordinate axis is an axis whose behavior follows that of a Cartesian coordinate system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Cartesian coordinate axis

owl:Class.terms:description: An x-axis is a Cartesian coordinate axis that is aligned with the horizon.
owl:Class.schema:comment: In most figures, this axis represents categories, such as months, market segments, or other non-numeric data.
owl:Class.resource:example: The horizontal axis in http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: x-axis

owl:Class.terms:description: A y-axis is a Cartesian coordinate axis that is spatially oriented perpendicular to the x-axis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: y-axis

owl:Class.terms:description: A z-axis is a Cartesian coordinate axis that is spatially oriented normal to the plane formed by the x- and y-axes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: z-axis

owl:Class.terms:description: A category axis is an axis in which the position along the line is partioned into categories.
owl:Class.resource:example: The horizontal axis corresponding to months of the year in graph 4 of http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: category axis

owl:Class.terms:description: A primary category axis is a category axis that either defines the sole value range or holds the larger set of categorical values specified by the secondary category axis.
owl:Class.resource:example: The category axis that corresponds to years in Graph 1 of http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: primary category axis

owl:Class.terms:description: A secondary category axis is a category axis that defines a finer granular part (or subset) of the value range of the primary category axis.
owl:Class.resource:example: The category axis that corresponds to months in Graph 1 of http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: secondary category axis

owl:Class.terms:description: A value axis is an axis in which the position along the line is partioned into numeric values.
owl:Class.schema:comment: A value axis holds the properties of having a minimum and a maximum value, and is usually associated with tickmarks that indicate intervals along the axis.
owl:Class.resource:example: The value axis that ranges from 3.0 to 7.4 and corresponds to billions of dollars in Graph 1 of http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: value axis

owl:Class.terms:description: A left value axis is a value axis that is spatially positioned to the left of the plot area.
owl:Class.resource:example: The value axis that ranges from 3.0 to 7.4 and corresponds to billions of dollars in Graph 1 of http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: left value axis

owl:Class.terms:description: A right value axis is a value axis that is spatially positioned to the right of the plot area.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: right value axis

owl:Class.terms:description: A scaled value axis is a value axis in which the value range was subject to a mathematic transformation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: scaled value axis

owl:Class.terms:description: A linear value axis is a value axis that corresponds to a scaling factor of 1 of the value range.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: linear value axis

owl:Class.terms:description: A logarithmic value axis is a scaled value axis that corresponds to a scaling factor of the logarithm of the value range.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: logarithmic value axis

owl:Class.terms:description: A data series is a data set composed of related values displayed in a statistical graph.
owl:Class.resource:example: Example: The two series that correspond to "Seasonally adjusted" and "Trend" are composed of the seasonally adjusted value of permits in each month and values from a trend derived from some mathematical tranformation across those values, respectively, in Graph 1 of http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: data series

owl:Class.terms:description: A data point is a point that which corresponds to the projection of the values of measurement data against the axes of a statistical graph.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: data point

owl:Class.terms:description: A global maximum stationary point is a data point that corresponds to a measurement value is larger than that of all other plotted datapoints.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: global maximal stationary point

owl:Class.terms:description: A global minimum data point is a data point that corresponds to a measurement value is smaller than that of all other plotted datapoints.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: global minimal stationary point

owl:Class.terms:description: A legend is a part of a figure that associates textual descriptions with symbols pertaining to plotted entities.
owl:Class.resource:example: The colored line segments and the adjacent textual descriptions in Graph 1 of http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: legend

owl:Class.terms:description: A primary title is a title that should be first used in describing some entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: primary title

owl:Class.terms:description: A secondary title is a title of lesser importance that should be used after the first title in describing some entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: secondary title

owl:Class.terms:description: scientific data is data obtained from some scientific procedure.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: scientific data

owl:Class.terms:description: A primary graph title is a primary title that describes a statistical graph.
owl:Class.resource:example: "Total value of permits increased slightly in December" in Graph 1 of http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: primary graph title

owl:Class.terms:description: A secondary graph title is a secondary title that describes a statistical graph.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: secondary graph title

owl:Class.terms:description: A phrase is a group of words functioning as a single unit in the syntax of a sentence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: phrase

owl:Class.terms:description: A clause consists of a subject and a predicate.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: clause

owl:Class.terms:description: A polygon vertex is a terminal point at which two polygon edges meet and are part of a polygon.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: polygon vertex

owl:Class.terms:description: A polygon edge is a line segment joining two polygon vertices.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: polygon edge

owl:Class.terms:description: A polyhedral skeleton is a collection of polygon edges.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: polyhedral skeleton

owl:Class.terms:description: A polygonal face is a polygon bounded by a circuit of polygon edges, and includes the flat (plane) region inside the boundary.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: polygonal face

owl:Class.terms:description: A polyhedral surface is composed of polygonal faces.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: polyhedral surface

owl:Class.terms:description: A polygon is a planar entity that is bounded by a closed path or circuit, composed of a finite connected sequence3 of straight line segments.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: polygon

owl:Class.terms:description: A geometric entity is an information content entity that pertains to the structure and topology of a space.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: geometric entity

owl:Class.terms:description: A point is a geometric entity that is located in a zero-dimensional spatial region and whose position is defined by its coordinates in some coordinate system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: point

owl:Class.terms:description: An endpoint is a terminal point that is the last of an ordered pair of points.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: endpoint

owl:Class.terms:description: A start point is a terminal point which is the first of an ordered pair of points.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: start point

owl:Class.terms:description: A model is a representation of some thing.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: model

owl:Class.terms:description: A line is curve that extends in a single dimension (e.g. straight line; exhibits no curvature), and is composed of at least two fully connected points.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: line

owl:Class.terms:description: A line segment is a line and a part of a curve that is (inclusively) bounded by two terminal points.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: line segment

owl:Class.terms:description: A tick mark is a line segment that is spatially positioned perpendicular to the axis of a statistical graph and indicates the position of a specific numeric value (which may be indicated by an adjacent value label) on a value axis, or is one of a pair of tick marks that delineates the boundary of a categorical value (which may be indicated by an adjacent category label) on the categorical axis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: tick mark

owl:Class.terms:description: A major tick mark is a tick mark that indicates the position of a specific numeric value and is adjacent to its value label on the value axis, or is one of a pair of tick marks that delineates the boundary of a categorical value indicated by an adjacent category label on the categorical axis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: major tick mark

owl:Class.terms:description: A minor tick mark is a tick mark that indicates the position of a specific numeric value but has no adjacent value label, or is one of a pair of tick marks that delineates the boundary of a categorical value but has no adjacent category label on the categorical axis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: minor tick mark

owl:Class.terms:description: A ray is a line which that is bounded by a startpoint and extends outwards infinitely along one dimension.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ray

owl:Class.terms:description: A quadrilateral is a polygon with composed of four points and four line segments, in which each point is fully connected to two other points.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: quadrilateral

owl:Class.terms:description: A rectangle is a quadrilateral in which one pair of line segments are parallel and the other pair are perpendicular to the first pair.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: rectangle

owl:Class.terms:description: A bar is a rectangle that is located in the plot of a statistical graph in which its length is proportional to the values that it represents.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: bar

owl:Class.terms:description: A triangle is a polygon composed of three points and three line segments, in which each point is fully connected to another point along through the line segment.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: triangle

owl:Class.terms:description: A directed line segment is a line segment that is contained by an ordered pair of endpoints (a start point and an endpoint).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: directed line segment

owl:Class.terms:description: An arrowed line is a directed line segment in which one or both endpoints is tangentially part of a triangle that bisects the line.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: arrowed line segment

owl:Class.terms:description: A single arrowed line is directed line in which the endpoint is tangentially part of a triangle that bisects the line.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: single arrowed line segment

owl:Class.terms:description: A double arrowed line is an arrowed line in which both terminal points are tangentially part of different triangles that bisect the line.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: double arrowed line segment

owl:Class.terms:description: A horizontal line is a line that is positionally oriented with the horizon.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: horizontal line

owl:Class.terms:description: A vertical line is a line that is positionally oriented perpendicular to the horizon.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: vertical line

owl:Class.terms:description: A trend line is a line, line segment or ray that is part of a statistical graph which indicates a statistical or visual direction across categorical or value data.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: trend line

owl:Class.terms:description: An increasing line is a line segment in which the startpoint and endpoint are ordered along one dimension and the difference of values in a second dimension is positive.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: increasing line

owl:Class.terms:description: An decreasing line is a line segment in which the startpoint and endpoint are ordered along one dimension and the difference of values in a second dimension is negative.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: decreasing line

owl:Class.terms:description: An plateau line is a line segment in which the startpoint and endpoint are ordered along one dimension and the difference of values in a second dimension is zero.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: plateau line

owl:Class.terms:description: A drop line is a statistical graph line that vertically or horizontally connects a data series line with a value axis in a statistical graph.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: drop line

owl:Class.terms:description: A terminal point is a point that defines the finite extension of a line.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: terminal point

owl:Class.terms:description: A surface normal is a vector that is perpendicular to a flat surface.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: surface normal

owl:Class.terms:description: A positionally oriented line is a line that is positioned against some axis of reference.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: positionally oriented line

owl:Class.terms:description: A statistical graph line is a line used in a statistical graph to communicate some trend or feature of the embedded data.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: statistical graph line

owl:Class.terms:description: An infinite line is a line that extends outwards in both directions of a single dimensional and is not bounded by terminal points.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: infinite line

owl:Class.terms:description: A vector is a line which that is bounded by a startpoint and extends outwards along one dimension.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: vector

owl:Class.terms:description: A vertext normal is the normalized average of the surface normals of the faces that contain that vertex.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: vertex normal

owl:Class.terms:description: A polyline is a connected sequence of line segments.
owl:Class.resource:hasSynonym: polygonal chain, polygonal curve, polygonal path, piecewise linear curve
owl:Class.rdfs:label: polyline

owl:Class.terms:description: A collection of points is a geometric entity that contains a non-zero set of geometric points.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: collection of points

owl:Class.terms:description: A diffusion equation describes density fluctuations in a material undergoing diffusion.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: diffusion equation

owl:Class.terms:description: A movement equation describes the displacement of an object in space over time.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: movement equation

owl:Class.terms:description: An ordinary differential equation (ODE) is a differential equation in which the unknown function (also known as the dependent variable) is a function of a single independent variable.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ordinary differential equation

owl:Class.terms:description: A partial differential equation (PDE) is a differential equation in which the unknown function is a function of multiple independent variables and the equation involves its partial derivatives.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: partial differential equation

owl:Class.terms:description: A differential equation is a mathematical equation for an unknown function of one or several variables that relates the values of the function itself and its derivatives of various orders.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: differential equation

owl:Class.terms:description: An idea is a proposition about some object of conceptual thought.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: idea

owl:Class.terms:description: structure is the specification that refers to the composition and arrangement of parts of an object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: structure

owl:Class.terms:description: A computational entity is an information content entity operated on using some computational system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: computational entity

owl:Class.terms:description: A curve is a geometric entity that may be located in n-dimensional spatial region whose extension may be n-dimensional, is composed of at least two fully connected points and does not intersect itself.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: curve

owl:Class.terms:description: A representation is a entity that in some way represents another entity (or attribute thereof).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: representation

owl:Class.terms:description: A ordinal position is a number that designates the position of an entity from the first entity in an ordered sequence of entities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ordinal position

owl:Class.terms:description: A collection is a set for which there exists at least one member, although any member need not to exist at any point in the collection's existence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: collection

owl:Class.terms:description: An empty set is a set for which there are exactly 0 members.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: empty set

owl:Class.terms:description: A standard is a socially-agreed upon specification.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: standard

owl:Class.terms:description: A regulatory authority is an organization responsible for exercising regulatory or supervisory capacity in some area of human activity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulatory authority

owl:Class.terms:description: A collective is a group of entities that share or are motivated by at least one common issue or interest, or work together on a specific project(s) to achieve a common objective.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: collective

owl:Class.terms:description: A formal specification is a mathematical description of software or hardware that may be used to develop an implementation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: formal specification

owl:Class.terms:description: An RDFS ontology is an ontology that conforms to the syntax and semantics of the Resource Description Framework Schema (RDFS).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RDFS ontology

owl:Class.terms:description: An OBO ontology is an ontology document as specified by the Open Biological Ontology community.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: OBO ontology

owl:Class.terms:description: chemical structure is the structure of a chemical entity in terms of its molecular geometry and electronic structure.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: chemical structure

owl:Class.terms:description: molecular structure is the spatial arrangement of atoms in a molecule and the chemical bonds that hold the atoms together.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: molecular structure

owl:Class.terms:description: A probability measure is quantity of how likely it is that some event will occur.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: probability measure

owl:Class.terms:description: A process model is a representation of some process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: process model

owl:Class.terms:description: An object model is a representation of an object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: object model

owl:Class.terms:description: A textual entity is language entity that is manifested as a sequence of one or more distinct characters.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: textual entity

owl:Class.terms:description: A version label is a label for a particular form or variation of an earlier or original type.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: version label

owl:Class.terms:description: A software version label is a version label for a piece of software.
owl:Class.resource:example: major.minor[.build[.revision]]
owl:Class.rdfs:label: software version label

owl:Class.terms:description: A start time is a time instant pertaining to the time at which a process begins.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: start time

owl:Class.terms:description: An end time is a time instant pertaining to the time at which a process ends.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: end time

owl:Class.terms:description: A unique identifier is an identifier that uniquely identifies some thing.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: unique identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: A justification is a proposition that defends, explains or excuses some argument.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: justification

owl:Class.terms:description: An academic department is a division of a university or school faculty devoted to a particular academic discipline.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: academic department

owl:Class.terms:description: institute is a society or organization having a object or common factor, and is normally applied to those with a scientific, educational, or social objective.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: institute

owl:Class.terms:description: A corporation is an organization that is granted a charter recognizing it as a separate legal entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: corporation

owl:Class.terms:description: A specification of an object, manifested by an agent, intended to accomplish goals, in a particular environment, using a set of primitive components, satisfying a set of requirements, subject to constraints.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: design

owl:Class.terms:description: A chemical identifier is an identifier for a chemical entity
owl:Class.rdfs:label: chemical identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: A record identifier is an identifier for a database entry.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: record identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: A physical entity identifier is an identifier for a physical entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: physical entity identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: An informational entity identifier is an identifier for an informational entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: informational entity identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: A molecular identifier is an identifier for a molecular entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: molecular identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: A curve segment is a part of a curve that consists of at least three points.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: curve segment

owl:Class.terms:description: A stationary point is a point that is part of a curve in which the derivative at that point is zero, and hence its value is at least a local maximum or minimum.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: stationary point

owl:Class.terms:description: A local maximum stationary point is a point that has a higher value in some axis than adjacent points.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: local maximum stationary point

owl:Class.terms:description: A local minimum stationary point is a point that has a lower value in some axis than adjacent points.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: local minimum stationary point

owl:Class.terms:description: A database is a set of tables.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: database

owl:Class.terms:description: A row represents a single, implicitly structured data item in a table.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: row

owl:Class.terms:description: A column is a vertical sequence of cells in a cellular automata.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: column

owl:Class.terms:description: A database table is a set of named columns with zero or more rows composed of cells that contain column values and is part of a database.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: database table

owl:Class.terms:description: The minimal unit of a cellular automaton that can change state and has an associated behavior.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: cell (informational)

owl:Class.terms:description: A database entry is a single, implicitly structured data item in a table.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: database entry

owl:Class.terms:description: A database collumn is a column in a database table.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: database column

owl:Class.terms:description: A unique cell is a cell that contains a unique value in the cellular automaton.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: unique cell

owl:Class.terms:description: A referenceing cell is a cell of a cellular automata that refers to another cell.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: referencing cell

owl:Class.terms:description: A referent cell is a cell that is the referent of some function or pointer.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: referent cell

owl:Class.terms:description: A database key is an informational entity whose value is constructed from one or more database columns.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: database key

owl:Class.terms:description: A primary database key is a database key that identifies every row of a table.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: primary database key

owl:Class.terms:description: A foreign database key is a database key that refers to a key in some table.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: foreign database key

owl:Class.terms:description: A p-value or probability value is the probability of obtaining a test statistic at least as extreme as the one that was actually observed, assuming that the null hypothesis is true
owl:Class.rdfs:label: probability value

owl:Class.terms:description: A street name is the token given to identify a particular street.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: street name

owl:Class.terms:description: A postal code is a geographic coordinate composed of a series of letters and/or digits appended to a postal address for the purpose of sorting mail.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: postal code

owl:Class.terms:description: An apartment number is the number assigned to identify an apartment in a building of apartments.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: apartment number

owl:Class.terms:description: The uncertainty value (margin of error) of a measurement is a range of values likely to enclose the true value.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: uncertainty value

owl:Class.terms:description: A standard deviation (represented by the symbol σ) is the quantity of variation from the average (mean, or expected value).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: standard deviation

owl:Class.terms:description: A versioned record is a record for which there exists another variant based that was derived via modification of the facts.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: versioned record

owl:Class.terms:description: An answer is a reply to a question.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: answer

owl:Class.terms:description: A verbal language entity is a language entity that is manifested through sound.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: verbal language entity

owl:Class.terms:description: A page number is the count of a page in a sequence of pages.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: page number

owl:Class.terms:description: A linear position is the position of some object against a linear positioning system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: linear position

owl:Class.terms:description: A sequence element position is the position of an element of a linear sequence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sequence element position

owl:Class.terms:description: A sequence start position is the start position for a sequence of characters.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sequence start position

owl:Class.terms:description: A sequence end position is the position of the last character in a sequence of characters relative to some linear frame of reference.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sequence end position

owl:Class.terms:description: The number of elements of a finite set of objects.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: count

owl:Class.terms:description: A Uniform Resource Locator or Universal Resource Locator (URL) is a specific character string that constitutes a reference to an Internet resource.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: URL

owl:Class.terms:description: An assocation is a relationship between two or more entities derived by some informational analysis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: association

owl:Class.terms:description: A statistical association is any relationship between two measured quantities that renders them statistically dependent.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: statistical association

owl:Class.terms:description: A top value axis is a value axis that is spatially positioned to the top of the plot area.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: top value axis

owl:Class.terms:description: A bottom value axis is a value axis that is spatially positioned to the bottom of the plot area.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: bottom value axis

owl:Class.terms:description: A chart is a figure that displays the relationship among tabular numeric data, functions or some kinds of qualitative structures.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: chart

owl:Class.terms:description: A map is a a visual representation of an area that depicts the relationship between elements of that space.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: map

owl:Class.terms:description: A heatmap is a graphical representation of data where the individual values contained in a matrix are represented as colors.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: heatmap

owl:Class.terms:description: A streamgraph is a multi-line stacked graph that yields the appearance of continuous y-values across the x-axis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: streamgraph

owl:Class.terms:description: A boxplot (box-and-whisker diagram) is a convenient way of graphically depicting groups of numerical data through their five-number summaries: the smallest observation (sample minimum), lower quartile (Q1), median (Q2), upper quartile (Q3), and largest observation (sample maximum).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: boxplot

owl:Class.terms:description: A geographic heatmap is a graphical representation of data over a geographic region where individual values are represented as colors.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: geographic heatmap

owl:Class.terms:description: A histogram is a graphical representation of data which consists of tabular frequencies, shown as adjacent rectangles, over discrete intervals (bins) , with an area equal to the frequency of the observations in the interval.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: histogram

owl:Class.terms:description: A measurement scale is a functional specification that specifies an allowed range of categories or values.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: measurement scale

owl:Class.terms:description: A nominal scale of measurement only specifies a limited set of categories.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: nomimal scale

owl:Class.terms:description: A binary scale is a measurement scale that specifies a choice between two values.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: binary scale

owl:Class.terms:description: A numeric scale of measurement is one that only specifies numeric values.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: numeric scale

owl:Class.terms:description: A decimal scale of measurement is one that only specifies decimal values.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: decimal scale

owl:Class.terms:description: An integer scale of measurement is one that only specifies integer values.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: integer scale

owl:Class.terms:description: An independent variable is a variable that may take on different values independent of other elements in a system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: independent variable

owl:Class.terms:description: A dependent variable is one whose value changes as a consequence of changes in other values in the system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: dependent variable

owl:Class.terms:description: A Gantt chart is a bar chart that illustrates a project schedule.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Gantt chart

owl:Class.terms:description: A correlation is a statistical relationship involving dependence between two random variables or datasets.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: correlation

owl:Class.terms:description: A television program is a audiovisual media that is produced and broadcast using a television.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: television program

owl:Class.terms:description: A pie chart is a circular chart divided into sectors each of whose length is proportional to the quantity it represents.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: pie chart

owl:Class.terms:description: A matrix chart summarizes a multidimensional data set in a grid.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: matrix chart

owl:Class.terms:description: A network diagram consists of a set of vertices connected by edges.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: network diagram

owl:Class.terms:description: A block histogram contains an x-axis that is divided into bins which correspond to value ranges. Each item in the data set is drawn as a rectangular block, and the blocks are piled into the bins to show how many values in each range.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: block histogram

owl:Class.terms:description: A bubble chart contains circles whose area corresponds to a value.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: bubble chart

owl:Class.terms:description: A stack graph is a statistical graph which presents multiple series in which the distance between one series and another indicates the relative contribution to the total for any x-value.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: stack graph

owl:Class.terms:description: A treemap is a chart that fully partitions the area into a set of rectangles whose area represents its relative value.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: treemap

owl:Class.terms:description: A word tree is a chart that links phrases with contexts through a tree-like branching structure.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: word tree

owl:Class.terms:description: A textual chart is a chart containing text.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: textual chart

owl:Class.terms:description: A tag cloud is a visualization of word frequencies.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: tag cloud

owl:Class.terms:description: A phrase net diagram illustrates the relationship between different words used in a text.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: phrase net diagram

owl:Class.terms:description: A mereological chart is a chart that illustrates the parts in the context of the whole.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: mereological chart

owl:Class.terms:description: A numeric label is a number used as a label.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: numeric label

owl:Class.terms:description: A start position is the proximal position of an object relative to an origin in a linear system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: start position

owl:Class.terms:description: An interval is a set of real numbers that includes all numbers between any two numbers in the set.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: interval

owl:Class.terms:description: A tree diagram is a hierarchical network diagram in which a root vertex is connected to one or more other vertices through a directed edge, which in turn may be connected to other vertices.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: tree diagram

owl:Class.terms:description: A flowchart is a diagram that represents an algorithm or process, showing the steps as boxes of various kinds, and their order by connecting these with arrows.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: flowchart

owl:Class.terms:description: A Venn diagram is a chart that illustrates all possible logical relations between a finite collection of sets as overlapping circles.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: venn diagram

owl:Class.terms:description: A dendrogram is a tree diagram used to illustrate the arrangement of the clusters produced by hierarchical clustering.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: dendrogram

owl:Class.terms:description: A default parameter is a parameter which has a default value.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: default parameter

owl:Class.terms:description: An end position is the distal position of an object relative to an origin in a linear system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: end position

owl:Class.terms:description: A standard operating procedure is a specification approved for use in specific environments.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: standard operating procedure

owl:Class.terms:description: A syllable is a verbal entity of language having one vowel sound, with or without surrounding consonants, forming the whole or a part of a word.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: syllable

owl:Class.terms:description: A consonant is a verbal entity of language that is articulated with complete or partial closure of the vocal tract.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: consonant

owl:Class.terms:description: A vowel is a verbal entity of language that is pronounced with an open vocal tract so that there is no build-up of air pressure at any point above the glottis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: vowel

owl:Class.terms:description: A sign language (also signed language) is a language that involves manual communication and body language to convey meaning. This can involve simultaneously combining hand shapes, orientation and movement of the hands, arms or body, and facial expressions to fluidly express a speaker's thoughts.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sign language

owl:Class.terms:description: A verbal language is a language that uses sounds to communicate.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: verbal language

owl:Class.terms:description: written language is a language that is communicated through a writing system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: written language

owl:Class.terms:description: A gene-disease association is an association between a gene and a disease.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: gene-disease association

owl:Class.terms:description: A chemical-disease association is an association between a chemical and a disease.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: chemical-disease association

owl:Class.terms:description: A diagnostic opinion is an opinion resulting from a medical diagnostic procedure.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: diagnostic opinion

owl:Class.terms:description: An opinion is a belief that is the result of emotion or interpretation of facts.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: opinion

owl:Class.terms:description: age is the length of time that a person has lived or a thing has existed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: age

owl:Class.terms:description: An ethnic group is a group of people whose members identify with each other through a common heritage, consisting of a common culture, including a shared language or dialect.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ethnic group

owl:Class.terms:description: A syndrome is composed of a set of several clinically recognizable features, signs (observed by someone other than the patient), symptoms (reported by the patient), phenomena or characteristics that often occur together.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: syndrome

owl:Class.terms:description: A ratio is a relationship between two numbers of the same kind expressed arithmetically as a dimensionless quotient of the two which explicitly indicates how many times the first number contains the second.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ratio

owl:Class.terms:description: A dose is the quantity of a chemical substance administered to a biological system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: dose

owl:Class.terms:description: effective dose is the amount of a substance required to produce an effect on a predefined percentage of a population.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: effective dose

owl:Class.terms:description: An expected value (or e-value) is the weighted average of all possible values that a random variable can take on.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: expected value

owl:Class.terms:description: A prognosis is a proposition about the likely course of a disease, the chance of recovery or recurrence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: prognosis

owl:Class.terms:description: A report is a textual document made that present focused, salient content to a specific audience.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: report

owl:Class.terms:description: A medical health record is a record of a single patient's medical history.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: medical health record

owl:Class.terms:description: A medical report is a report prepared by a health care practioner about test outcomes or health status of an individual.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: medical report

owl:Class.terms:description: A peer reviewed article is an article that has undergone peer-review and deemed acceptable for publication.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: peer reviewed article

owl:Class.terms:description: A major version number is a version of a software that exhibits a significant change in functionalilty from a prior version.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: major version number

owl:Class.terms:description: A minor version number is a version of a software that exhibits minor features or significant fix from a prior version.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: minor version number

owl:Class.terms:description: A revision number is a version of a software in which bugs have been fixed from a prior version.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: revision number

owl:Class.terms:description: A morpheme is the smallest semantically meaningful unit in a language.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: morpheme

owl:Class.terms:description: A study design is a protocol for the proper execution of a study which normally requires a carefullly crafted research question or hypothesis and at least one variable under observation and observed values for that variable.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: study design

owl:Class.terms:description: A recipe is a set of instructions that describe how to prepare or make something.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: recipe

owl:Class.terms:description: An experimental protocol is an action specification with respect to the design and implementation of experiments. In addition to providing a detailed set of procedures and lists of required equipment and instruments, experimental protocols often include information on safety precautions, the calculation of results and reporting standards, including statistical analysis and rules for predefining and documenting excluded data to avoid bias.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: experimental protocol

owl:Class.terms:description: A reason is a justification that specifies the motive for an action or a determination.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: reason

owl:Class.terms:description: The ordinal position of a character in a sequence of characters.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: character position

owl:Class.terms:description: The position of the first character in a word as an offset from the first character of the text in which it is found.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: word start position

owl:Class.terms:description: word end position is the position of the last character in a word as an offset from the first character of the text in which it is found.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: word end position

owl:Class.terms:description: A population is all the organisms that both belong to the same group or species and live in the same geographical area.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: population
